pr_body: This will focus on constructing a Web GUI for Reconstruction pipeline. The reconstruction pipeline takes RMN images as input and processes them, then produces files that are compatible with TVB. We Integrated the Web GUI with workflow engine (Pegasus) in order to provide job status and job execution statistics.
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 441473696, 'comment_body': 'This set of tags (label + input + i) can be moved to a generic component called InputField that receives as arguments the label ('openmp.threads'), the value ({this.state["openmp.threads"]}) and the title description.
Once we have such a method, we could transform all the code from lines 52-106 into a loop that iterates over the state and generates an InputField component with the proper label and title.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 17, 11, 25, 4, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'popaula937', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 441475594, 'comment_body': 'These 4 components (Configuration1, Configuration2, Configuration3 and Configuration4) are similar and have duplicated code. It would be very nice to extract a single component called PatientConfiguration that receives an argument to determine the current patient.
Inside the PatientConfiguration you could determine that argument from props and use it in the requests you send towards the server.   ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 17, 11, 28, 58, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'popaula937', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 441476931, 'comment_body': 'Here you should also extract a generic component, similar to the comment I left in Configuration.js', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 17, 11, 31, 45, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'popaula937', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 441477512, 'comment_body': 'Same as comment in Patient1/InputFiles.js', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 17, 11, 33, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'popaula937', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 441477680, 'comment_body': 'Same as comment in Patient1/InputFiles.js', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 17, 11, 33, 20, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'popaula937', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 441477820, 'comment_body': 'Same as comment in Patient1/InputFiles.js', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 17, 11, 33, 38, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'popaula937', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 441479255, 'comment_body': 'Instead of having this hardcoded string, you could define another function that generates the proper path by receiving as argument the current patient.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 17, 11, 36, 29, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'popaula937', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 441481136, 'comment_body': 'Instead of defining 4 endpoints in the server, one for each patient, you could define a single one that receives as argument the current patient and does all the computation generically.
As a result, you will not have duplicated code here, there will be fewer lines of code and this file would be easier to read. Thus, it will also be easier to maintain: if you need to do a change, you will not have to do it 4 times, in each of the endpoints, but a single time in the generic endpoint.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 17, 11, 40, 14, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'popaula937', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 441481540, 'comment_body': 'This endpoint could also be generic and receive the current patient as an argument.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 17, 11, 40, 58, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'popaula937', 'type': 'User'}]
